  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>basmati rice</strong> and 250ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[500ml] </span><strong>cold water</strong> to a pot with a lid and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until all the water has been absorbed and the rice is cooked, then remove from the heat and keep covered until serving</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1640000226588-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1640000226588-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1640000226588-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1640000226588-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1640000226588-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Tip: This is to warm your tortillas later – alternatively, add them to a plate and pop in the microwave for 1-2 min</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>beef mince</strong> with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until browned, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1640000232913-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1640000232913-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1640000232913-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1640000232913-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1640000232913-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the mince is cooking, chop the <strong>tomato<span class=\"text-danger\">[es]</span></strong> finely</p><p>Cut the<strong> lime<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> in half</p><p>Combine the juice of 1/2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[1]</span><strong> lime</strong> with the <strong>mayo</strong> and a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>in a small bowl</p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> – this is your<strong> lime mayo</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1640000237382-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1640000237382-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1640000237382-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1640000237382-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1640000237382-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once browned, add the<strong> smoked paprika</strong> and <strong>chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) to the beef and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped tomato</strong>,<strong> chipotle paste</strong> (not a fan of spice? Just add a little!) and <strong>honey</strong> and cook for 3-5 min or until the tomato begins to break down and the beef becomes crispy and sticky – this is your<strong> sticky chilli beef</strong></p>",
